This paper focuses on optimizing the performance of a 3D lattice Boltzmann solver on third generation nVidia GPU hardware, which involves a combination of computational efficiency and memory transfer optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.SC (Symbolic Computation), and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
